Here’s a simplified version of the `publishStep` code:
typescript
const publishStep = createStep({
  id: 'publish',
  execute: async ({ inputData }) => {
    const { blog, weeklyData } = inputData;

    // 1. Create Notion page with a title
    const createResult = await createNotionPage({
      title: `Weekly Recap: ${blog.headline}`
    });
    const notionPageId = createResult.id;

    // 2. Create DEV.to draft first to get its edit link
    const devtoResult = await createDevtoArticle({
      title: blog.headline,
      body_markdown: buildDevtoMarkdown(blog),
      tags: blog.tags,
      published: false
    });
    const devtoEditLink = devtoResult.edit_url;

    // 3. Build planner markdown with DEV.to link and weekly data
    const plannerMd = buildPlannerMarkdown(weeklyData, blog, {
      devtoLink: devtoEditLink,
      notionPageUrl: `https://www.notion.so/${notionPageId}`
    });

    // 4. Write structured markdown to Notion page
    await writeNotionMarkdown(notionPageId, plannerMd);

    return { notionPageId, devtoEditLink };
  }
});

Key points: The DEV.to draft is created *before* the Notion page content is written to ensure the Notion planner can include a link to the draft for easy access.
